     <font class="TallRed">A question for the ladies...<a name="109185387631195853">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          Note that I have not been fucked over myself (recently, anyways). In fact, I have neither time nor tolerance for romance. Partly, this is because antipsychotics do a pretty tough job on your sex drive, partly because I've failed enough that I simply see no point in trying.<br /><br />So here's the question: What's so hard about saying no to a guy?<br /><br />Here's the male perspective: Suppose I like you, and suppose that you don't like me. If that is the case, then for god's sake, TELL ME! I realize that you think it will hurt me. Yes, in fact, this is true. But it hurts a hell of a lot more when you lead me on. The longer you pretend, the more shit will be hitting the fan when the truth comes out.<br /><br />Why do you lead me on? Is it because you haven't decided on an answer yet? If this is the case, I don't have a problem, but then this is not leading me on either. Why do you say "maybe" when you already know you mean "no"?<br /><br />Comments enabled; I hope for some honest replies.<br />
