     <font class="TallRed">Internet: the New Heroin, Adventures in Music, and much more!<a name="109167502372774531">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          So, it occurs to me that a may have a slight internet addiction. It's too easy to just get on Slashdot or Wikipedia and just keep clicking more and more links... it never ends! It's kind of cool, in a way, because I'm learning a lot of things; then again, I haven't been going outside as much as I probably should be. Now I know how to classify a star by its color or tell a sparrow from a warbler, but I haven't really looked at either since I learned this stuff. I've kind of been letting everything else suffer a little... I'm never very good with the whole concept of "balance", I suppose. It's at least good that I get addicted to the internet and video games instead of drugs or alcohol, but in some respects it's kind of the same. At least it's making me better at crossword puzzles.<br /><br />What IS cool though is that I'm playing a rock show/festival in Winchester on the 13th of this month with a band called Divider. Fans of Exploding Boy might know them better as "the band formerly known as One Day Forever", as Exploding Boy played a few shows with them back in the day. They're very good musicians and awesome guys, and everyone should come out and see the show. What sucks is that I missed band practice today, after being zonked into unconsciousness by stupid allergy medicine. I'm just going to have to practice real hard this week... their bass player is real good anyway, so I have some sizeable shoes to fill.<br /><br />I've been listening to the Decemberists a lot lately, and I highly recommend them to everyone. They're one of those bands that are incredible and nobody really knows about them (see also: Red House Painters). Their vocalist always reminds me of Zach, from Old Hat, and that's always a plus.<br /><br />In other news, I might just be going away to the old Radford University in the fall. It wasn't my first choice, but it's in a beautiful area, and it's supposed to have a better music program than Tech. What sucks is that some of my credits won't transfer until I finish my Associates degree... which means finishing my three final and most despicable classes: Health/PE, Intro to Speech, and Orientation. Yes, they're all first semester classes that I've put off until now. Dammit.<br /><br />Alright, I'm off to a small weeknight party that will surely turn into the kind of party where the girls get mad because the guys are playing Halo instead of talking to them. Woohoo! Arrghblingblingbling. Sorry.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.defenselink.mil/news/jul2004/n07272004_2004072705.html">The Soldiers of the Future (link borrowed from Slashdot)</a><br /><br />
